# Data Vis

We can calculate like, infinite generations of any given grid.  So, if we start at a gridsize of 1x1, can we simulate every position on every given starting orientation of every possible grid dimensions.  Can we also calculate if a given starting orientation will ever settle?  Sample for X generations and a loop is defined as....? 


Detecting the loop seems like the non-trivial part of this plan.  Loops can have a period of >400, which would mean storing thousands? of grid states, and checking if they ever equal? Are there aperiodic loops? Probably not, since the state could be considered a starting orientation, so it should always resolve to the same if it is indeed a loop.

But, if we can get these problems solved, we can sim every starting orientation to see if it eventually ends in a loop.  Plot the 3d (heatmap?) yes/no % per x/y grid, see if something neat pops out.

## want to know:

how many generations we can theoretically store
how quickly we can sim generations
best way to store states

## possible speedup
store known loops with their smallest possible grid size, then set that as a loop for every x, y for the rest of the search.  check map before calculating anything.

